<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kenneth R. Weiss 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 HOLDING OFFICE: San Diego County Dist. Atty. Edwin L. Miller Jr., the dean of 
California prosecutors, faces stiff competition this election after his office 
bungled a high-profile case . . . . If he's toppled this year, Ventura County's 
Michael D. Bradbury would become California's longest-serving D.A. in a major 
county. As in the past three elections, Bradbury has no opponent. "I'm 
beginning to think I'm the only one dumb enough to want this job," Bradbury 
said. "Seriously, I think it is the best job in the world." 
</P>
<P>
 DIRTY JOB: Wielding a three-handled shovel, Simi Valley leaders on Thursday 
symbolically broke ground on the city's long-awaited Cultural Arts Center . . . 
. If all goes as planned, the old Community Methodist Episcopal Church on Los 
Angeles Avenue will be transformed into a 290-seat theater with an art gallery 
by next February. And, construction costs will peak at $2.5 million. Work began 
on the site a few days before the official groundbreaking, Deputy City Manager 
Bob Heitzman said. "We needed some soft dirt to turn, so we had to do some 
grading first." 
</P>
<P>
 POWERHOUSE: At 6-foot-1 and about 285 pounds, Dolores Tuimoloau stands out in 
more than one sport at Oxnard's Channel Islands High School. But the attentions 
lavished on the 18-year-old senior by college recruiters focus on the local 
records she has shattered in the shotput (C12). "She has had so many calls from 
so many schools," Coach Myra Beemis says. "I lost track." And the shotput is 
her off-season sport. Dolores' heart belongs to basketball. A center, she 
intimidates opponents with her size. 
</P>
<P>
 INSULT TO INJURY: Imagine being in a car accident. You're unconscious and 
being wheeled into the hospital emergency room on a gurney. And a hospital 
clerk picks your pocket . . . . That happened to several patients at St. John's 
Regional Medical Center before authorities arrested Michelle Elaine Peralta of 
Oxnard. Peralta got 90 days in jail for going on a shopping spree with credit 
cards swiped from emergency-room patients (B1). 
</P>
