<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; STAGE SHOW OFFICIALS SEEK HOST FAMILIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Temporary homes are being sought for cast members of Up With People, an 
international stage ensemble that will perform at Mission Viejo High School on 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The musical show is sponsored by the city Rotary Club, which will use the 
proceeds to support its scholarship program. 
</P>
<P>
 One of five touring casts, the musical group is composed of about 150 young 
people from 22 different countries. The performers, between 17 and 25, visit up 
to a dozen countries during the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers hope to find host families to feed, house and provide 
transportation for cast members to Mission Viejo High School between Monday and 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 "Because we're a nonprofit organization, it's impossible for us to stay in 
hotels," group spokesman Garry Poisson said. "But it's also a great learning 
experience for the students." 
</P>
<P>
 A few of the countries cast members come from include Sweden, Estonia, Poland 
and Spain, Poisson said. 
</P>
<P>
 "There are some real interesting exchanges," he said. "The students learn 
about cultures from all over the world." 
</P>
<P>
 The show will take place at the high school, at 25025 Chrisanta Drive, 
beginning at 7:30 p.m. The cost is $9 for adults, $7 for students and senior 
citizens. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets can be purchased at the high school box office. 
</P>
<P>
 Dubbed "The World in Motion," the show takes place during a mock global 
satellite broadcast and features a broad range of international and local dance 
and music. 
</P>
<P>
 Included in the program is a medley of music from mariachi to gospel and rock. 
</P>
<P>
 For information about the show or becoming a host family, call (714) 
458-2336.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
