<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; TASK FORCE SEEKS PEOPLE IN BUSINESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Members of the business community are being sought to join a community task 
force. 
</P>
<P>
 The nine-member group will investigate how to improve the business climate in 
San Juan Capistrano in several areas, including persuading local merchants and 
companies to stay in the city, attracting new businesses and making the 
downtown district more appealing to shoppers. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials say the task force will meet every two weeks and will make 
recommendations to the City Council.  
</P>
<P>
 Those interested should call Douglas Dumhart or Cassandra Walker in City Hall 
at (714) 493-1171. The forms must be filed by June 16.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
