<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; CITY REGISTERING KIDS FOR DAY CAMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's Community Services Department is now registering campers for the 
"Funtime Day Camps" at Edison and Murdycommunity centers. 
</P>
<P>
 The first weeklong camp will begin June 27.The camps are designed for children 
age 6 to 12 and offer a range of activities, including arts and crafts, 
bowling, baseball and swimming. Seven, one-week sessions will be offered from 
8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Monday through Friday.  
</P>
<P>
 The cost is $95 for one week. 
</P>
<P>
 Camp highlights will also include outdoor games, miniature golf, water slides 
and bumper boats. Youngsters will also take a boat cruise, a trip to the beach 
and visit a major amusement park. Daily fruit snacks and drinks are included in 
the fee. 
</P>
<P>
 Extended day care will also be offered at Murdy Community Center for an 
additional $25 a week. Hours will be 7:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Transportation for day campers will be available from Edison Community Center 
for an additional $6. 
</P>
<P>
 More information is available by calling or stopping by Edison Community 
Center, 21377 Magnolia Ave., (714) 960-8870, or Murdy Community Center, 7000 
Norma Drive, (714) 960-8895. 
</P>
</TEXT>
