WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; RESIDENTS WARNED OF AIDS CHARITY SCAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man walking door to door in Port Hueneme claiming to be collecting money for 
children suffering from AIDS is actually running a scam, police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Over the past week, police have been investigating reports of a man who has 
collected money from Port Hueneme residents after he said he was representing a 
charity called California Christian Community Services. 
</P>
<P>
 The charity apparently does not exist, according to Port Hueneme Police 
Detective Ken Dobbe. The information that the man gave to residents included a 
false phone number and address. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want the public to be aware that this is going on as a warning to them, 
and so they can notify us if he makes another appearance," Dobbe said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dobbe advised that people who are contacted by someone claiming to be from the 
charity should call the police at 986-6530. MATTHEW MOSK 
