<P>
ARGENTINE STAR MARADONA SAYS HE MAY QUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Diego Maradona, disgusted over suggestions that he dictates the team's roster, 
threatened Thursday to quit Argentina's World Cup team. 
</P>
<P>
 The soccer star spoke in response to a radio interview with the mother of 
defender Dario Franco, who was left off the team. 
</P>
<P>
 Franco's mother told radio station La Red her son was not placed on the team 
because Maradona "dictates the lineup to (Coach Alfio) Basile." Basile said 
Franco was excluded because of a leg injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Maradona, speaking from Austria, where Argentina plays a tuneup game Saturday, 
said: "My nerves are in a terrible state, I can't go on like this." 
</P>
<P>
 He said he would call his wife today before deciding. 
</P>
