<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD PARK; ZAAHI BREAKS HIND LEG AND HAS TO BE DESTROYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Zaahi, who was to have raced in the $300,000 Californian on Sunday at 
Hollywood Park, had to be destroyed after breaking down during a workout there 
Thursday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 A 5-year-old son of Slew O' Gold, Zaahi broke his right hind leg. 
</P>
<P>
 Owned by Shadwell Stable and trained by Neil Drysdale, Zaahi had four 
victories in 19 starts and earnings of $356,680. Raced primarily in Europe 
before he was shipped to California last year, he finished third in the 
Kensington Handicap in his final start May 1 at Golden Gate Fields. 
</P>
<P>
 A field of six is likely when entries for the 1 1/8-mile Californian are taken 
this morning. The Wicked North, Del Mar Dennis, Stuka, Kingdom Found, Thunder 
Rumble and Slew Of Damascus are the probable starters. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 With Golden Gate Fields shifting its post time on Fridays to 4 p.m. for the 
rest of its meeting, Hollywood Park will offer two simulcasts from there 
tonight. The first is scheduled for 6:42, before Hollywood Park's first post at 
7. The other will be shown between Hollywood Park's first and second races. BOB 
MIESZERSKI 
</P>
