<P>
BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tenneco Inc. to Spin Off 25% of J.I. Case Unit: The Houston company, one of 
the nation's largest conglomerates, said it will sell part of the farm and 
construction equipment unit next week in a stock offering worth between $335 
million and $385 million.In a filing with the Securities and Exchange 
Commission, Tenneco revised downward the number of Case shares it will offer to 
17.5 million, or 25% of Case shares, from a previously planned 24.5 million, or 
35%. They are expected to go on sale at between $19 and $22 a share on the New 
York Stock Exchange. The new company name will be Case Corp. 
</P>
