ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DANA POINT; POLICE SEEKING MAN WHOM CHILDREN FLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies are looking for a man who has allegedly harassed children 
in Del Obispo Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Frightened youngsters reported that a man in his early 20s tried to converse 
with them May 25 at the park, causing them to flee, according to authorities. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was apparently trying to gain their confidence by engaging (them) in 
conversation," said sheriff's Lt. Dan Martini. 
</P>
<P>
 The man was also seen at the park, on Del Obispo Street near Pacific Coast 
Highway, on at least one occasion in March. 
</P>
<P>
 Martini said witnesses indicated the man spent time watching the children 
before approaching them. 
</P>
<P>
 "We'd like to talk with him to find out what his interest is in these 
children," Martini said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man is described as 5-foot-8 and about 160 pounds, with dark brown or 
black shoulder-length hair. Investigators say his face has acne scars. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information is asked to call Deputy Mark Simon at (714) 647-7449 
or Sheriff's Department Investigators Steve Sharpe or Joe Homs at (714) 
248-3552. FRANK MESSINA 
