<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; CITY TO BAN SMOKING AT PUBLIC FACILITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Burbank City Council has voted to ban smoking in all publicly owned and 
operated facilities as early as July. 
</P>
<P>
 The ban, approved in a 4-0 vote this week, prohibits people from lighting up 
in such facilities as City Hall and much of the Starlight Amphitheatre, in 
city-owned vehicles and within five feet of any entrance or exit to a municipal 
building. Ashtrays will soon be removed from municipal buildings and signs 
prohibiting smoking will be posted. VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
