<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SEAL BEACH; REPAIRS TO PIER WILL BEGIN TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Workers will begin making repairs today to the Seal Beach Pier, which was 
damaged in a fire on May 21. 
</P>
<P>
 The historic wood boardwalk will remain closed for at least 15 more days 
during the first part of the repairs.By then, city officials hope to have 
enough lumber to complete a second and final set of repairs. 
</P>
<P>
 If officials can't get enough wood by the end of June, they plan to place a 
temporary ramp over the burned portion and reopen it through the busy summer 
tourist season. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire, which temporarily trapped more than 100 people at the end of the 
boardwalk, caused at least $350,000 in damages. No one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire burned several wood supports and crossbeams, some of which must be 
replaced. Fire investigators suspect that the blaze started when charcoals from 
a grill fell below the boardwalk and ignited a gas line. 
</P>
<P>
 The damage was covered by insurance, but the city must pay a $100,000 
deductible. SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</TEXT>
