<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: HOMEOWNERS GROUPS FIGHT AIRPORT NOISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three homeowners associations are distributing thousands of flyers containing 
the telephone numbers that people can call to lodge complaints about aircraft 
noise from Van Nuys and Burbank airports. 
</P>
<P>
 Homeowners associations from Encino, Studio City and Valley Village are 
mailing and handing out 8,000 flyers that urge people to "lay the foundation 
for changes in flight patterns." 
</P>
<P>
 The mailing is the latest campaign in the homeowners' ongoing feud with the 
airports over aircraft noise. Gerald Silver, an outspoken activist on the 
issue, has called for drastic cuts in helicopter operations out of Van Nuys 
Airport. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are doing it to provide a public service, to make it easy for people to 
determine the correct phone numbers," said Silver, president of the Homeowners 
of Encino. "I'm hoping it will alert the airport to the gravity of the 
situation." 
</P>
<P>
 Silver said that circulars are being mailed out now because people are more 
likely to hear the noise as the weather gets warmer and they spend more time 
out on the patio or leave their windows open. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are heavily impacted," said Tony Lucente, president of the Studio City 
Residents Assn., which is distributing 6,000 of the flyers. "People are really 
uptight about this issue." KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</TEXT>
