<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TUSTIN; SCHOOL DISTRICT APPOINTS PRINCIPAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Tustin Unified School District has appointed Louise Saladino principal of 
Robert P. Heideman Elementary School. She will begin July 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Saladino will replace Pat James, who was recently named assistant principal at 
Columbus Tustin Middle School. 
</P>
<P>
 Saladino has been in public education for 19 years. She is currently the 
principal of Jordan Elementary School in the Orange Unified School District. 
She had been a principal at two other Orange Unified elementary schools -- 
Silverado and Esplanade. 
</P>
<P>
 Saladino began her career in 1975 at the Montebello Unified School District 
teaching reading, math, arts and a variety of other subjects for kindergarten 
to eighth-grade students. In 1984, she joined the Fullerton School District as 
assistant principal at Nicolas Junior High School. 
</P>
<P>
 She has been with the Orange Unified School District since 1986. She holds a 
bachelor's degree in social sciences and a master's degree in educational 
administration from Whittier College. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
