ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BREA; MAYOR PLANS TO SEEK REELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mayor Glenn G. Parker has announced that he will seek reelection to a second 
term in November. 
</P>
<P>
 "Although I have achieved a significant number of the goals that I committed 
to pursue when elected in 1990," Parker said in a prepared statement, "there 
are some long-terms goals" yet to pursue. He cited the future of the hillsides 
to the city's north, development and implementation of a revised Parks and 
Recreation Master Plan, and the completion of the downtown redevelopment 
program. 
</P>
<P>
 Parker, 41, is the owner of Brea-based Park Glen Community Management Inc., 
which provides management services to homeowner associations. ALAN EYERLY 
