<HEADLINE>
<P>
BECKMAN INSTRUMENTS SIGNS VIETNAM MARKETING AGREEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Beckman Instruments Inc. said Thursday that it has signed a dealer agreement 
to market its products in Vietnam. 
</P>
<P>
 The dealer, Europ Continents, also buys and resells Beckman equipment in Laos 
and Cambodia. Fullerton-based Beckman makes diagnostic equipment for hospitals 
and bioresearch equipment for life sciences laboratories. 
</P>
<P>
 The Asia-Pacific market, which makes up 13% of Beckman's business, is the 
fastest-growing region in the medical equipment industry, the company said. As 
Asian economies improve, growing middle classes are demanding better health 
care, said Louis Rosso, chairman and chief executive of Beckman. Universities 
and national research centers in Asia are also expanding and increasing demand 
for the company's products, he said. 
</P>
