<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mortgage Rates Rise: Thirty-year, fixed-rate mortgages averaged 8.55% this 
week, up from 8.53% last week, according to a national survey released by the 
Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp. The average hit a 25-year low of 6.74% in 
October. Fifteen-year mortgages averaged 8.02% this week, up from 7.99% a week 
earlier. On one-year, adjustable-rate mortgages, the average initial rate rose 
to 5.52%, from 5.48% last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
