BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 BP to Sell California Service Stations to Tosco: BP Oil Co., a subsidiary of 
London-based British Petroleum Co., said it will sell 128 service stations, 
four non-operating stations, five vacant properties and a distribution terminal 
to the Connecticut-based refiner for $82 million. Tosco Corp. will retain the 
BP logo on the stations, which are mostly in Northern California. 
</P>
