<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cybernetics Products Inc.: The Santa Ana-based maker of high-technology 
manufacturing tools, computerized machinery controls and precision camera and 
scanning equipment said it has acquired a 53% equity interest in Vision Ten, a 
New Jersey medical imaging equipment company. 
</P>
<P>
 Cybernetics said it will issue about 160,000 shares of its common stock to 
Vision Ten shareholders and will retire a $650,000 Vision Ten note by issuing 
an additional 216,666 shares of Cybernetics common to the note-holder. 
</P>
<P>
 The acquisition will not affect Cybernetics' employment in Orange County, 
where 45 people work in the corporate headquarters and a manufacturing 
division. Another 55 people are employed in divisions in Connecticut and New 
Jersey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
